<h2>Star-studded Kids Help Children Event to Benefit PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center</h2>


<p>The stars will be out Sunday, Aug. 19  for &ldquo;Kids Help Children,&rdquo; a fun-filled day of music and teen celebrities to be  held from 2 to 5 p.m. at the Hilton Hotel in Anaheim, Calif. The  family-friendly fundraiser will benefit PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention  Center. </p>
<p>  Among the young stars scheduled to  attend are Kenton Duty (&ldquo;Shake It Up!&rdquo;), Dakota Hood (&ldquo;Hunger Games&rdquo;), Ryan  Ochoa (&ldquo;iCarly&rdquo;), and Stefanie Scott (&ldquo;A.N.T. Farm&rdquo;). After the stars make  their way down the red carpet, attendees will have the opportunity to meet  their favorite celebrities, get autographs, and have their pictures taken with  the stars. Throughout the afternoon, guests can enjoy balloon artists, bounce  houses, face painting, visiting animals from SeaWorld, and more. There will also  be a concert featuring Savvy &amp; Mandy (Radio Disney), Austin Anderson (&ldquo;Victorious&rdquo;),  and Temara Melek, plus other surprise performers. </p>
<p>&ldquo;We are so appreciative of the work  so many people have put into planning this event,&rdquo; said Julie Hertzog, director  of PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s wonderful that all of  these teen celebrities are willing to give their time and talent to support  bullying prevention.&rdquo;</p>
<p>  Following the event, which is  sponsored by DirecTV and Papa John&rsquo;s Pizza, the celebrity guests will be  recording public service announcements in support of PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying  Prevention Month in October. To purchase tickets, or learn more about the event  (including a complete list of scheduled celebrity attendees), visit <a href="http://www.KidsHelpChildren.com" target="_blank"><strong>www.KidsHelpChildren.com</strong></a>.</p>
<p>  For more information on the work of  PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center, visit PACER.org/bullying.</p>
